<div class="p-4 bg-white rounded-3 shadow-sm">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p><strong>Data Sources:</strong> RAWG Video Games Database API, Steam Store APIs, Faker.</p>
  <p>
    The RAWG API is a canonical game metadata (name, release date, rating) plus relationships to genres, platforms, and developers. JSON responses with pagination.
  </p>
  <p>
    Steam Store API used for recent user review snippets and helpfulness. JSON payload under reviews.
  </p>
  <p>
    Faker used for fallback descriptions and extra titles to exceed the 200-row minimum and for development.
  </p>
  <h3 class="mt-4">The Database ERD</h3>
  <pre>
    Game (id, rawg_id, steam_appid, name, slug, released, rating, description, created_at, updated_at)
    Genre (id, name, slug, created_at, updated_at)
    Platform (id, name, slug, created_at, updated_at)
    Developer (id, name, slug, created_at, updated_at)
    Review (id, game_id, author, content, source, rating, created_at, updated_at)

    GameGenre (game_id, genre_id)           -- PK: (game_id, genre_id)
    GamePlatform (game_id, platform_id)     -- PK: (game_id, platform_id)
    GameDeveloper (game_id, developer_id)   -- PK: (game_id, developer_id)

    Associations:
    Game 1—* Review
    Game *—* Genre      (via GameGenre)
    Game *—* Platform   (via GamePlatform)
    Game *—* Developer  (via GameDeveloper)
  </pre>
</div>